cdx6500PPCTdot5PortTable.name: cdx6500PPCTdot5PortTable
cdx6500PPCTdot5PortTable.description: This table contains Token Ring interface parameters and state variables, one entry per 802.5 interface.

cdx6500PPCTdot5PortEntry.name: cdx6500PPCTdot5PortEntry
cdx6500PPCTdot5PortEntry.description: A list of Token Ring status and parameter values for an 802.5 interface.

cdx6500dot5IfIndex.name: cdx6500dot5IfIndex
cdx6500dot5IfIndex.description: This object is the port number for the LAN Interface.

cdx6500dot5LanCableType.name: cdx6500dot5LanCableType
cdx6500dot5LanCableType.description: Specifies the type of cable and therefore which connector is used for LAN interface. utp : Unshielded twisted pair stp : Shielded twisted pair. newvalUtp : same functionality as 'utp', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500dot5PortMacAddress.name: cdx6500dot5PortMacAddress
cdx6500dot5PortMacAddress.description: Specifies the MAC address of the LAN port. The entered value of 00-00-00-00-00-00 will be replaced by the Burned In Address (BIA) if the LAN hardware is present.

cdx6500dot5LocalRingNumber.name: cdx6500dot5LocalRingNumber
cdx6500dot5LocalRingNumber.description: This parameter specifies the local ring number to which this port is attached. It is used as default if a value is not obtained from Ring Parameter Server.

cdx6500dot5EarlyTokenRelease.name: cdx6500dot5EarlyTokenRelease
cdx6500dot5EarlyTokenRelease.description: This parameter controls whether this station operating on a 16 Mbps ring will perform early token release. This parameter has no effect for 4 Mbps rings where early token release is not used. newvalDisable : same functionality as 'disable', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500dot5TransmitQueueLimit.name: cdx6500dot5TransmitQueueLimit
cdx6500dot5TransmitQueueLimit.description: Number of frames that can be queued on the transmitter before any frame is dropped.

cdx6500PPSTdot5PortTable.name: cdx6500PPSTdot5PortTable
cdx6500PPSTdot5PortTable.description: A table containing Token Ring statistics, one entry per 802.5 interface. All the statistics are defined using the syntax Counter as 32-bit wrap around counters. Thus, if an interface's hardware maintains these statistics in 16-bit counters, then the agent must read the hardware's counters frequently enough to prevent loss of significance, in order to maintain 32-bit counters in software.

cdx6500PPSTdot5PortEntry.name: cdx6500PPSTdot5PortEntry
cdx6500PPSTdot5PortEntry.description: An entry contains the 802.5 statistics for a particular interface.

cdx6500dot5StatsIfIndex.name: cdx6500dot5StatsIfIndex
cdx6500dot5StatsIfIndex.description: The value of this object identifies the 802.5 interface for which this entry contains management information.

cdx6500dot5StatsPortType.name: cdx6500dot5StatsPortType
cdx6500dot5StatsPortType.description: The currently running value of the Port type.

cdx6500dot5StatsDataBytesRx.name: cdx6500dot5StatsDataBytesRx
cdx6500dot5StatsDataBytesRx.description: This counter is incremented for each data byte received by the LAN port.

cdx6500dot5StatsDataBytesTx.name: cdx6500dot5StatsDataBytesTx
cdx6500dot5StatsDataBytesTx.description: This counter is incremented for each data byte transmitted by the LAN port.

cdx6500dot5StatsFrameSizeExc.name: cdx6500dot5StatsFrameSizeExc
cdx6500dot5StatsFrameSizeExc.description: This counter is incremented when the LAN port observes a frame that can not be forwarded because of excessive length.

cdx6500dot5StatsShortFrames.name: cdx6500dot5StatsShortFrames
cdx6500dot5StatsShortFrames.description: This counter is incremented when the LAN port observes a receive or transmitted frame which is less than 18 bytes.

cdx6500dot5StatsTransmitDiscards.name: cdx6500dot5StatsTransmitDiscards
cdx6500dot5StatsTransmitDiscards.description: This counter is incremented when the LAN port discards the frame because the transmit queue exceeds the maximum queue length.

cdx6500dot5StatsPortStatus.name: cdx6500dot5StatsPortStatus
cdx6500dot5StatsPortStatus.description: Indicates the status of the LAN port. newvalDisabled : same functionality as 'disabled', new enumeration added for RFC1155 compatibility.

cdx6500dot5StatsLastStatReset.name: cdx6500dot5StatsLastStatReset
cdx6500dot5StatsLastStatReset.description: Time stamp when the statistics were last reset.

cdx6500dot5StatsClearStats.name: cdx6500dot5StatsClearStats
cdx6500dot5StatsClearStats.description: This is the command to reset the LAN port statistics.
